00:12:16.620 --> 00:12:21.670
So first, what is this
idea of Bazgasht?

00:12:21.670 --> 00:12:23.420
How did it come to be?

00:12:23.420 --> 00:12:25.390
Well the classification of
Persian literary history

00:12:25.390 --> 00:12:27.830
and its development,
particularly now we're talking

00:12:27.830 --> 00:12:31.430
about poetry can be traced back
to this man, Muhammad Taqi Bahar

00:12:31.430 --> 00:12:35.510
who died in 1951, a great poet
and literary historian of Iran.

00:12:35.510 --> 00:12:38.220
And what he does is he
divides the development

00:12:38.220 --> 00:12:41.400
of Persian literary
culture, particularly poetry

00:12:41.400 --> 00:12:44.470
into four schools or styles each

00:12:44.470 --> 00:12:46.800
with its own literary
characteristics

00:12:46.800 --> 00:12:49.530
and roughly corresponding to
different periods in history.

00:12:49.530 --> 00:12:52.360
So you have the Khurasani
School, the Iraqi School,

00:12:52.360 --> 00:12:55.900
the Indian style and
Literary Return.

00:12:55.900 --> 00:12:57.920
Now which period is given a name?

00:12:57.920 --> 00:13:01.900 position:56%
It maintains a core set of stylistic
attributes and is affiliated

00:13:01.900 --> 00:13:03.560
with a different temple or period.

00:13:03.560 --> 00:13:05.940
And even Bahar recognizes
that there's some slippage

00:13:05.940 --> 00:13:09.830
between these terms, but as far
as talking about the core elements

00:13:09.830 --> 00:13:13.740
of development over a period of
time he does a fairly good job

00:13:13.740 --> 00:13:17.440
in distinguishing between say
the Khurasani School which tends

00:13:17.440 --> 00:13:21.060
to be located at the core of the
praise of a patron, deals very kind

00:13:21.060 --> 00:13:25.440 position:56%
of naturalistically, talks about the
hunt and feasting and merrymaking.

00:13:25.440 --> 00:13:29.760
And praise the patrons
of beneficence and glory

00:13:29.760 --> 00:13:32.570
versus the Iraqi School which
tends to be the poetry associated

00:13:32.570 --> 00:13:35.330
with Hafiz and Rumi and
is more inward looking,

00:13:35.330 --> 00:13:38.970
more mystical which Bahar and
others would say kind of stems

00:13:38.970 --> 00:13:42.590
from destructive practices
of the monguls leading

00:13:42.590 --> 00:13:46.080
into a more introspective
type of poetry production.

00:13:46.080 --> 00:13:50.160
The Indian style which we'll talk
about in just a moment is known

00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:54.570
for its intellectualism, its
mannerism, its abstract acrobatics,

00:13:54.570 --> 00:13:56.890
it's complicated metaphors.

00:13:56.890 --> 00:14:00.840
And then finally, Literary Return
is already mentioned is referencing

00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:04.830 position:56%
this group of Iranian poets and is
exclusively Iranian poets who sought

00:14:04.830 --> 00:14:06.870
to return to the simple
ways of the Masters.

00:14:06.870 --> 00:14:12.110
So we sought the return back to
poetry Ferdowsi, Sadi and Hafiz,

00:14:12.110 --> 00:14:16.570
those poets of the
Khurasani and Iraqi school.

